msgctxt "sn36.15:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.15:0.2"
msgid "2. Rahogatavagga"
msgstr "2. In Private"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 15. Paṭhamaānandasutta → santakasuttaṃ (bj) | santakaṃ 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.15:0.3"
msgid "15. Paṭhamaānandasutta"
msgstr "15. With Ānanda (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.220"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.15:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi, ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha … sat down to one side, and said "
"to him:"

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.2"
msgid ""
"“katamā nu kho, bhante, vedanā, katamo vedanāsamudayo, katamo vedanānirodho, "
"katamā vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what is feeling? What’s the origin of feeling? What’s the cessation of "
"feeling? What’s the practice that leads to the cessation of feeling?"

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.3"
msgid "Ko vedanāya assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan”ti?"
msgstr "And what is feeling’s gratification, drawback, and escape?”"

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.4"
msgid "“Tisso imā, ānanda, vedanā—"
msgstr "“Ānanda, there are these three feelings:"

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.5"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.6"
msgid "imā vuccanti, ānanda, vedanā."
msgstr "These are called feeling."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.7"
msgid "Phassasamudayā vedanāsamudayo;"
msgstr "Feeling originates from contact."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.8"
msgid "phassanirodhā vedanānirodho."
msgstr "When contact ceases, feeling ceases."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.9"
msgid ""
"Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The practice that leads to the cessation of feelings is simply this noble "
"eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.10"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.11"
msgid "Yaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ vedanāya assādo."
msgstr ""
"The pleasure and happiness that arise from feeling: this is its "
"gratification."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.12"
msgid "Yaṃ vedanā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ vedanāya ādīnavo."
msgstr ""
"That feeling is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.13"
msgid ""
"Yo vedanāya chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ vedanāya nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Removing and giving up desire and greed for feeling: this is its escape."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.14"
msgid "Atha kho panānanda, mayā anupubbasaṅkhārānaṃ nirodho akkhāto."
msgstr "But I have also explained the progressive cessation of conditions."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.15"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vācā niruddhā hoti … pe …"
msgstr "For someone who has attained the first absorption, speech has ceased. …"

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.16"
msgid "saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannassa saññā ca vedanā ca niruddhā honti."
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling, "
"perception and feeling have ceased."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.17"
msgid ""
"Khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgo niruddho hoti, doso niruddho hoti, moho niruddho "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"For a mendicant who has ended the defilements, greed, hate, and delusion "
"have ceased."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.18"
msgid "Atha kho panānanda, mayā anupubbasaṅkhārānaṃ vūpasamo akkhāto."
msgstr "And I have also explained the progressive stilling of conditions."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.19"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vācā vūpasantā hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the first absorption, speech has stilled. …"

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.20"
msgid "saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannassa saññā ca vedanā ca vūpasantā honti."
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling, "
"perception and feeling have stilled."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.21"
msgid ""
"Khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgo vūpasanto hoti, doso vūpasanto hoti, moho "
"vūpasanto hoti."
msgstr ""
"For a mendicant who has ended the defilements, greed, hate, and delusion "
"have stilled."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.22"
msgid "Atha kho panānanda, mayā anupubbasaṅkhārānaṃ paṭippassaddhi akkhātā."
msgstr "And I have also explained the progressive tranquilizing of conditions."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.23"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vācā paṭippassaddhā hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the first absorption, speech has been "
"tranquilized. …"

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.24"
msgid "ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samāpannassa rūpasaññā paṭippassaddhā hoti."
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the dimension of infinite space, the perception "
"of form has been tranquilized."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.25"
msgid ""
"Viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samāpannassa ākāsānañcāyatanasaññā paṭippassaddhā hoti."
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the dimension of infinite consciousness, the "
"perception of the dimension of infinite space has been tranquilized."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.26"
msgid ""
"Ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samāpannassa viññāṇañcāyatanasaññā paṭippassaddhā hoti."
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the dimension of nothingness, the perception of "
"the dimension of infinite consciousness has been tranquilized."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.27"
msgid ""
"Nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samāpannassa ākiñcaññāyatanasaññā paṭippassaddhā "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the dimension of neither perception nor non-"
"perception, the perception of the dimension of nothingness has been "
"tranquilized."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.28"
msgid ""
"Saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannassa saññā ca vedanā ca paṭippassaddhā honti."
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling, "
"perception and feeling have been tranquilized."

msgctxt "sn36.15:1.29"
msgid ""
"Khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgo paṭippassaddho hoti, doso paṭippassaddho hoti, "
"moho paṭippassaddho hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For a mendicant who has ended the defilements, greed, hate, and delusion "
"have been tranquilized.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.15:1.30"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
